flowchart TB
  subgraph Client[Frontend: React SPA (Vite + Tailwind)]
    NAV[Navbar]
    P1[Dashboard]
    P2[Analytics]
    P3[About]
    P4[Services]
    P5[Contact]
    NAV --> P1
    NAV --> P2
    NAV --> P3
    NAV --> P4
    NAV --> P5
  end

  subgraph API[Backend: Node.js + Express]
    E[/POST /api/events/]
    M[/GET /api/metrics/]
    MR[/GET /api/metrics/recent/]
    S[/POST /api/sim/start | /stop | /generate/]
    PROC[Event Processor]
    MET[Metrics Aggregator]
    IO((Socket.io))
  end

  subgraph Store[Persistence]
    MYSQL[(MySQL)]
    MEM[[In-Memory Store]]
  end

  SIM[Simulator (IDs 101–110)] --> S
  DEV[Driver Devices] --> E

  E --> PROC
  PROC --> MYSQL
  PROC --> MEM
  PROC --> IO

  MET --> M
  MYSQL --> MET
  MEM --> MET
  MR --> Client

  IO --> P1
  IO --> P2
  M --> P1
  M --> P2

  P1 --- K1[Metrics Cards]
  P1 --- K2[System Status]
  P1 --- K3[Alerts & Event Log]
  P1 --- K4[Charts (Recharts)]

  P2 --- A1[Top Drivers]
  P2 --- A2[Distribution by Type]
  P2 --- A3[Avg Speed by Type]
  P2 --- A4[Violations per Minute]
  P2 --- A5[Violations by Hour]
  P2 --- A6[Risk Score Trend]
  P2 --- A7[Top Risky Trips]

sequenceDiagram
  participant Sim as Simulator
  participant Dev as Driver Device
  participant Api as Express API
  participant Proc as Event Processor
  participant Db as MySQL/In-Memory
  participant Ws as Socket.io
  participant Ui as React UI

  Sim->>Api: POST /api/sim/generate
  Dev->>Api: POST /api/events { driver_id, trip_id, event_type, speed }
  Api->>Proc: process(event)
  Proc->>Db: insert(event, risk_score)
  Proc->>Ws: emit new_driver_event(event)
  Ui->>Api: GET /api/metrics/recent
  Api-->>Ui: events[]
  Ws-->>Ui: new_driver_event(event)
  Ui->>Ui: update metrics, alerts, charts
